      1          /**
      2           *  @file       
      3           *
      4           *  @brief      Glitch Filter
      5           *
      6           *  @details    This module removes Glitches of signals.
      7           *  <pre>
      8           *      Basically if the input signal comes above or below the last measurement by more than a configurable threshold
      9           *      the output signal will still the same as the previews sample for a configurable number of iterations.
     10           *      If the signal stays out of the threshold for long enough them the output signal will be updated by the input signal.
     11           *  </pre>
     12           *
     13           *
     14           *  $Header: GlitchFilter.c 1.2 2014/09/03 12:02:41BRT MANOEL GARBUIO DE SOUZA (SOUZAMG) Exp  $
